# The presence of this file makes `npm pack` ignore .gitignore, so the
# generated `template/` snapshot SHIPS. The `files` allowlist in package.json
# already scopes the tarball to `src` + `template`; this file just makes sure
# the build-time/dev-only bits never sneak in.
#
# Do NOT add exclude patterns here. They are NOT anchored, so a bare pattern
# like `scripts/` or `tsconfig.json` would also strip those paths from inside
# `template/` (e.g. template/packages/backend/scripts/setup-auth-env.ts), which
# would ship a broken scaffold. The `files` allowlist in package.json already
# excludes the scaffolder's own scripts/, tsconfig.json, and tests from the tarball.
